name: Tswapong Serpent
shortLoreBlurb: Tswapong Serpent is a spirit/serpent from Botswana associated with cave python, rain. Serpents mark thresholds and hidden wisdom. Appeased for safe passage and rains.
overlapsLinks: Fafnir (Norse), Jörmungandr (Norse), Manannán (Celtic), Naga (India/SE Asia), Poseidon (Greek), Quetzalcoatl (Aztec), Tangaroa (Polynesia), Yemaya (Yoruba)
